      <div class="starter-template">
	<h3>Methods:</h3>
	<p> We use a lexicon-based Sentiment Analysis to assign a “polarity” to each pamphlet in which major players in the Revolution are mentioned. This method involves parsing phrases where the figure in question is referenced for terms expressing some sentiment and comparing those terms to a pre-determined lexicon. Each word in the lexicon is assigned a score corresponding to positive, negative, and neutral emotion with the polarity defined as the ratio of positive to negative scores. Using this straightforward method to translate each pamphlet into a set of scores allows for a wide range of statistical analysis that would be impossible to do any other way, especially considering the sheer number of pamphlets. Furthermore, this technique will translate emotional expression into a form that lends itself to visual storytelling.</p>
	
      </div>
